<Base title="About — Jiageng Wang">
  <article class="post">
    <h1 style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Jiageng (Will) Wang, an M.Sc. Analytics student at Nanyang Technological
      University, Singapore, and a research intern at the Institute for Infocomm
      Research (I²R), A*STAR. My research sits at the intersection of
      <strong>LLM agents and electronic design automation</strong>: building
      training-free agent frameworks that make language models reliable in
      high-stakes, expert domains like analog circuit design.
    </p>
    <p>
      Before Singapore, I earned a B.Eng. in Aerospace Engineering at Sun Yat-sen
      University and worked as an AIGC algorithm engineering intern at Keyone AI in
      Shenzhen, where I shipped a production Photoshop plugin and deployed
      diffusion models under restricted-network environments.
    </p>
    <p>
      Alongside research, I follow the broader AI-agent landscape — frameworks,
      evaluation, and real-world deployment — which shows up in the writing on
      this blog.
    </p>

    <h2>中文</h2>
    <p>
      我是王家赓(Will),南洋理工大学分析学硕士在读, A*STAR 资讯通信研究院(I²R)研究实习生。
      研究方向是 LLM Agent 与电子设计自动化(EDA)的交叉:构建免训练的智能体框架,
      让大语言模型在模拟电路设计这类高风险专家领域中变得可靠、可验证。
    </p>
    <p>
      此前本科毕业于中山大学航空航天工程专业,曾在深圳 Keyone AI 担任 AIGC 算法工程实习生。
      业余关注 AI Agent 方向的进展,博客会记录研究笔记、工程实践与观察思考。
    </p>

